ed.","test_description":"Wire service + geocoding adapter fake + optimizer module in-process. Provide addresses where one geocode call returns empty results; assert optimized route excludes that stop and response includes exactly that address in skipped list.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate addresses in the input list are consolidated into a single stop with combined delivery items, not visited twice.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is data handoff between deduplication/aggregation and routing stages: duplicates must merge items, then downstream route must contain one visit. Testing only a local dedupe helper can miss pipeline regressions where optimizer still receives/produces duplicates. No real OS/network/subprocess is required, no AI/ML dependency, and no multi-agentic chain. Rejected System: behavior text does not require real external infrastructure; in-process module wiring reproduces the failure mode.","test_description":"Run service with duplicated address inputs carrying distinct item lists. Assert output has one consolidated stop with merged items and route visit count for that address equals one.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
